A phase portrait of  shown in Fig.  exhibits
typical chaotic structure.  Chaotic behavior arises naturally when two
or more scalar fields interact with each other in an expanding
Universe, but it is usually of a transient
type. The observed chaotic oscillations in the present model, on the
contrary, are persistent.  Even after quite large excursions
 and  always find back to each
other.  This kind of intermittent coincidence holds true for the whole
decay of  from the very large
values before inflation down to very small values like those of today.

