Obviously the chaotic nature of the system is still quite structured,
because roughly the two frequencies  and 
remain visible as organizing factors. It is well known that in linear
systems with two incommensurable frequencies ergodic phase portraits
are obtained. It appears that the chaoticity of the present system is
caused by a permanent change of the ratio .
In this process, due to the overwhelming abundance of irrational
numbers, the change between different measures of incommensurability
leads to a certain amount of unpredictability.

Because it was not possible to calculate the full evolution from
inflation to the present state, the time-averaged coincidence of
 and  claimed above was tested piecewise
in more than ten different -regimes from very large to very
small, starting with many different values of the ratio 
 in each.  Fig.  shows 3 typical
examples.


